==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[black]] [[and]] [[tan]]|-}}

# A beverage made from a dark (black) and a light (tan) malt beverage.  The typical black and tan is made of Guiness or Beamish stout (black) and Bass or Harp ale (tan).  The barkeep will first pour half a glass of the darker, heavier liquid.  This is done slowly to prevent a thick head from forming.  Once the bottom layer has settled, the light liquid is poured over the back of an inverted spoon to fill the glass.  When a black and tan is poured correctly the division between light and dark is very clean with little or no mixing.